I'm usually so hesitant to be sure about lip-synching but this is definitely auto-tuned, over a pre-recording, post-produced, or live-corrected. Their voices don't match movements, get tired, falter, or have any imperfections like in the instances of real live vocals. It sounds JUST LIKE the studio version, so it probably is. It is too manufactured to perfection, which is a shame because they have the vocal talent but SM keeps doing this to keep up the image.

Don't get me wrong, Red Velvet's one my fav old girl groups and aligned with MAMAMOO, they're the definition of a vocal group. They nailed, delivered, even surpassed themselves here (some notes could get even better than the ones in the studio released version), but sometimes I felt like there was an effect in their voices when they're singing together or harmonizing to keep the voices in sync and feel like blended, which is not a problem at all though, just something I noticed because thankfully when they sing their individual lines, I couldn't listen anything more than their voices (better than ever here). Regardless of any of this, Red Velvet hold their crown of THE vocal group

Their Velvet side is second to none. I love their R&B style.  These songs should have been more popular in the USA in my opinion.  You don't need to understand to the words necessarily to enjoy the arrangement. I played Kingdom Come at a party two years ago and people lost their minds.  If I was a promoter or someone with lots of money, I would book an event at the Apollo Theater in New York and call it "Korean Seoul/ K-Seoul". Then have the most popular Korean R&B songs (old and new) performed for an American audience.  Not like the kiddie K-Pop concerts in the past.  I would focus this among a more mature audience. If I could get Crush, Zion-T, Red Velvet, and others, it would be a good concert.

RV : REAL VOICE â¤
RV : REAL VOICE â¤
I have a confession to make: I used to hate Red Velvet back then during their debut. It was that time when EXO was messy following the news of Kris' departure from the group then followed by Tao and Luhan. 2014 was a pure heartbreak in a perspective of an EXO-L. I was devastated as a fan and little did I know that I was pouring my hate on these girls. I used to see them as SM's scapegoat.   But now, watching this video, I can't help but cry when they started singing their debut song "Happiness". How can I possibly despise this song back then when it was so good? How can I hate these girls when all they deserve was genuine support and overflowing love? I hated myself for blaming them back then. And now, I loved them even more. You girls rock! RED VELVET IS A MASTERPIECE. PERIODT.  P.S. I started being fan when Yeri was added to the group HAHAHAAHAHAHAHA

my ears filled with happiness, thank you Red Velvet
Some people insisting this is either lip syncing/pre-recorded vocals/auto-tuned/pre corrected pitch must be the same people who are too used to their kpop faves frequently using these aid that even hearing singers perform the simplest songs sounds like autotune to them lol.  Some of these songs are not even that hard to sing as long as you have the right technique and style (which RV have mastered as a group). I bet they would sing the easiest songs and still be accused for using autotune just because. XD  On this performance, it's normal to hear prerecorded parts or playback because it's either the member harmonized their own lines (so they cant technically harmonize their ownself at the same time live singing the lines unless they have kage bunshin technique) OR the studio version of that line/part has heavy effects (like Wendy's last part of Let it Shine where it is synthed in the last part after the sustained note). Those things cant be helped but deciding that everything in the performance is not real raises another point of discussion -Killing Voice is a show where they invite amazing artists to sing a selection of some of their best hits live. The stage set up is good as a recording studio making them sound like the studio version. So saying that RV are "not really singing" is basically saying Killing Voice actually cooperated in faking their singing which is basically an insult to the credibility of the program.  I'd understand those dissatisfied with their dancing but to say that their performance relied on autotune/pitch corrector and whatnots like really? Being in the industry for 10years and training for how many years before debuting just to fake perform? Is it really that hard to comprehend that Red Velvet are just simply skilled enough to control their singing dynamics considering that they come from a company that have the most strict vocal training? I mean with their versatility, unique vocal colors and diverse sound wouldn't be getting a lot of praises from music critics and collab offers from a lot of producers just for being fake right? Lol make it make sense. Imagine being bored in life and coming here just to throw nonsense comments with an obvious intent of discrediting everyone's hardwork. Red Velvet fans are not delusional. Haters are.

According to the Holy Bible, ALL have sinned and fallen short of the glory of God, and the wages of sin is death (Romans 6:23). The unrighteous will not inherit the kingdom of God. After death comes judgment, and we ALL deserve to go to hell because we are all guilty of breaking God's perfect law. It is written in Proverbs 14:12 that there is a way which seems right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death. Many people are trusting in other ways for salvation, deceiving themselves that they can get to heaven on their own accord, instead of placing their faith in the one true God alone for salvation.  Because man is sinful, he is separated from God, who is holy and perfect (Isaiah 59:2). Because our Heavenly Father loves us, He bridged this gap of separation by sending His Son, Jesus, to die on the cross in our place to pay the penalty for our sins. Jesus is God who dwelt among us. He is the Messiah who was spoken of by the Old Testament prophets. Jesus fulfilled the law and conquered death, and He shall return again. We must individually RECEIVE Jesus Christ as our Savior and Lord. Our Heavenly Father wants us to BELIEVE on the one whom He has sent (John 5:24). Make no mistake, there is no other way to Heaven but through Jesus Christ (John 14:6). For it is by grace through faith that you have been saved, the FREE GIFT of God to those will accept it (Ephesians 2:8-9). If you have not placed your faith in Jesus alone as the Savior, I pray that today may be the day of your salvation.  The Gospel (the Good News) 1 Corinthians 15: 1-4 Moreover, brethren, I declare unto you the GOSPEL which I preached unto you, which also ye have received, and wherein ye stand; By which also ye are SAVED, if ye keep in memory what I preached unto you, unless ye have believed in vain. For I delivered unto you first of all that which I also received, how that Christ DIED for our SINS according to the scriptures; And that He was BURIED, and that He ROSE again the third day according to the scriptures.

God sent his Son, Jesus, to Earth as a perfect sinless sacrifice. To take on all the sins of the world; both past, present, and future sins. Shedding his blood on the cross as a blood atonement for all sins. After dying on the cross, he rose from the dead on the 3rd day and rose to Heaven. To show life after death. To show everlasting life through Jesus's sacrifice. John 14:6 states: "Jesus saith unto him, I am the way, the truth, and the life: no man cometh unto the Father, but by me.". Romans 10:13 states "For whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.".      Eternal life in heaven is just one prayer away. Please don't let pride drag you into eternal punishment in Hell, but ask Jesus to give you eternal life in Heaven. He wants you in Hell for all eternity with him. Hell is not a fun place, like worldly people like to imagine. It's everlasting torture with no relief. Keeping people from thinking about salvation. Keeping you from thinking about life after death. Please, ask Jesus into your hearts to save you of your sins and cleanse you from all unrighteousness. Yang paling berkuasa mengatur seluruh dunia  &  akhirat adalah Pencipta Dunia. (semua manusia di seluruh dunia diciptakan oleh Pencipta yang sama.   Tapi di dunia ada banyak      agama      &   aliran kepercayaan serta ada juga yang atheis.      Siapakah Pencipta manusia    &   dunia ?   Banyak orang mengakui bahwa Pencipta Dunia  itu antara lain    :    Maha  Kuasa ,  Maha  Kasih.    Maka Pencipta Dunia memberitahu siapa diriNya,  pasti dengan cara yang sangat / paling mudah.    Supaya manusia bisa dengan sangat mudah juga mengetahui Pencipta manusia).        Pemilik  Dunia  =  Pemilik  Akhirat    Pengatur  Dunia  =  Pengatur  Akhirat  ( kalau pemilik rumah,  paling berkuasa  mengatur  +  buat  peraturan  untuk orang - orang yang menghuni / mengontrak rumahnya )

Red Velvet transcends time with their mesmerizing blend of voices. ğŸ¤âœ¨  One of the most magical aspects of Red Velvet lies in the seamless fusion of their voices. Each member brings a unique color to the group, creating a harmonious symphony that captivates listeners. From the powerhouse vocals of Wendy to the soulful tones of Seulgi, the angelic voice of Joy, the sweet melodies of Irene, and the charismatic voice of Yeri, Red Velvet's vocal palette is truly a masterpiece.  Red Velvet has consistently demonstrated a musical prowess that is ahead of its time. Their genre-defying tracks showcase a willingness to experiment with diverse sounds and styles, from the bold and quirky "Red" side to the sultry and sophisticated "Velvet" side. This versatility not only keeps fans on their toes but also positions Red Velvet as pioneers in the ever-evolving landscape of K-pop.  While Red Velvet has amassed a dedicated fan base, there's a sentiment among some fans that the current generation might not fully appreciate the group's groundbreaking contributions. Their ability to seamlessly transition between concepts, coupled with their vocal prowess, makes them a standout group that deserves recognition not just for their popularity but for their artistic depth.  Red Velvet's journey in the K-pop scene has been nothing short of SPECTACULAR. Whether it's their chart-topping hits, visually stunning music videos, or unforgettable live performances, Red Velvet has consistently proven why they deserve the title of the best K-pop group. Their impact on the industry is undeniable, and their influence is felt not only in South Korea but around the globe.  In a world where trends come and go, Red Velvet remains a timeless gem, leaving an indelible mark on the hearts of fans. So, let's take a moment to appreciate the extraordinary voices, the avant-garde concepts, and the unparalleled talent that Red Velvet brings to the K-pop stage. Here's to Red Velvet, the true pioneers of K-pop brilliance! ğŸŒˆğŸ‘âœ¨

Anyone else thinking this?

Oh Boy, Lady's Room, Oh boy, Feel My Rhythm:  "In a realm where dreams take flight, A tapestry of colors so bright, You better know, my dear, We're here to spread joys and cheer.  With laughter and sweet harmonies, We dance to the beat, feeling free, Happiness like ice cream cake, Delighting in each slice we take.  Through melodies of red flavor, We explore a world to savor, Peek-a-boo, we play the game, Seeking thrills, never quite the same.  Riding with the bold and the tough, Embracing life with a spirit rough, Bad boy vibes that set hearts ablaze, Leaving a trail of electrifying maze.  Enter the gates of Queendom grand, Where power and grace firmly stand, Oh boy, here reigns the lady's room, A sanctuary, a mystical bloom.  Feel my rhythm, let it intertwine, With the pulse of the divine, For within these verses you'll see, The magic that lies inside of me.  In this lyrical symphony we compose, A tapestry of emotions that expose, The beauty that is poetry's might, Guiding us through both day and night." ì§„ì§œ ë²„ë¦´ ê³¡ì´ ì—†ë‹¤.. ì•¨ë²” ë‚´ë©´ ì „ê³¡ ë‹¤ ë“¤ì–´ë³´ëŠ” ëª‡ ì•ˆë˜ëŠ” ê°€ìˆ˜!!!!!!!! ë ˆë“œë²¨ë²³ ì˜ì›í•´ì¤˜ Êšâ™¡É
Kenapa aku nangis ya nonton ini? Rasanya baru kemaren mereka debut. Red Velvet dan SNSD adalah 2 grup yg selalu ada di hatiku. SNSD di masa SD dan SMP, Red Velvet di masa SMA. Ga kerasa banget udah 9 tahun lebih mereka menemani hari-hariku mulai dari SMA sampai sekarang udah umur 25 tahun. Mereka adalah hal spesial di masa remaja menuju dewasaku. Lagu - lagu mereka punya arti tersendiri di tiap kenangan. Lagu terfavourite waktu sma itu Day 1, lagu yg ceria selalu aku dengar tiap mau pergi ke sekolah. Waktu kuliah aku suka banget lagu Eyes Locked Hands Locked. Dan masih banyak lagi lagu-lagu yg sangat indah dari mereka. Lagu senang, lagu sedih, semuanya bagus dan sangat masuk di telinga dan hatiku. Terimakasih Red Velvet untuk 9 tahun yg indah ini. I love you with all my heart.  Love, Yemima

And finally, seulgi was able to debut as a member of Red Velvet as a main dancer and lead vocal, even now she is able to write a song, rap, and even act.
